designation: Lecturer, School of Computer Science and Engineering
biography: Prior to joining NTU, Dr Josephine Chong has previously worked at the Northumbria University (England) and Auckland University of Technology (New Zealand). While working at these universities, she teaches a range of Business Information Systems modules such as Business Information Systems, Enterprise Information Systems, Business Database Management and SAP. Her main research interest focuses on digital transformation and specially how organizations can redesign their strategies and frameworks for data analytics capability.
